Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.41,0:00:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe is vast and awe-inspiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.79,0:00:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth and life on it are amazingly complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.47,0:00:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it all get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.60,0:00:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible book of Genesis says\Nthat there is a Creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.52,0:00:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But the account is often misunderstood\Nor even dismissed as a myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.61,0:00:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is what the Bible says\Nabout the origin of the universe plausible?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.99,0:01:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Scientists estimate that the universe\Nis 14 billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.04,0:01:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This implies that the universe,\Nincluding earth, had a beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.21,0:01:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible agrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.22,0:01:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis 1:1 reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.51,0:01:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the beginning God created\Nthe heavens and the earth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.56,0:01:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The account does not say\Nwhen or how the universe began.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.02,0:01:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, it focuses
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.07,0:01:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,on the creative process\Nthat took place on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.53,0:01:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,over six periods of time,\Nwhich the Bible calls days.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.66,0:01:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Were these six 24-hour days, as many believe?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.66,0:01:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.29,0:01:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hebrew word used in the Bible for “day”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.29,0:01:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,can refer to various lengths of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.17,0:01:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis even summarizes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.92,0:01:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the six days of creation as one day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.30,0:01:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—“the day that Jehovah God\Nmade earth and heaven.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.43,0:02:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Each “day” in Genesis chapter 1
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.93,0:02:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,must have spanned\Nextremely long periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.77,0:02:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The account’s perspective is also important.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.86,0:02:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The writer describes the creative periods
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.03,0:02:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as they would have appeared\Nto an observer on the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.58,0:02:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Had someone been there,\Nhe would have seen events
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.41,0:02:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that started in one period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.46,0:02:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and then progressed\Ninto the following periods.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.34,0:02:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Light penetrated the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.96,0:02:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to reveal alternating day and night.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.38,0:02:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth was covered with water,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.26,0:02:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and vapor filled the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.81,0:02:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The dense clouds lifted\Nfrom the waters that covered the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.98,0:02:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,forming an expansive sky between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.48,0:02:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Water receded to uncover dry ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.69,0:02:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and the first plants appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.20,0:02:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The atmosphere cleared further
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.16,0:03:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to reveal the sun and the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.08,0:03:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,God created living creatures in the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.87,0:03:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and flying creatures above.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.38,0:03:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the last period,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.50,0:03:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,God created land animals and humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.26,0:03:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In harmony with the Genesis account,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.14,0:03:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible says:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.52,0:03:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Of course, every house\Nis constructed by someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.11,0:03:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but the one\Nwho constructed all things is God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.28,0:03:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible does not speak\Nin scientific detail,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but its account of creation\Nis logical and reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.66,0:03:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible also offers\Nlogical and reasonable answers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.50,0:03:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to other important questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.42,0:03:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Does our planet exist for a purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:03:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.47,0:04:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What does the future hold?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.26,0:04:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,To see the Bible’s answers, go to jw.org®
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.81,0:04:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,or fill out the online request\Nfor one of Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.60,0:04:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to visit at a time\Nand place convenient for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.70,0:00:18.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,宇宙は広大で神秘的です
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.17,0:00:27.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,地球と生物の造りは驚くほど複雑です
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.34,0:00:32.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらはどのように始まりましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.47,0:00:42.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の創世記には\N天地創造の記録があります
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.73,0:00:45.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかしそれは間違って解釈され
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.40,0:00:48.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,作り話だと見なされています
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.20,0:00:55.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,宇宙の誕生に関する\N聖書の記録は科学的でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.99,0:01:01.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,科学者によると 宇宙の年齢は\Nおよそ140億年です
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.21,0:01:07.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり 地球を含め\N宇宙には始まりがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.42,0:01:14.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書にも 創世1章1節で\Nこう書かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.93,0:01:19.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,「初めに 神は天と地を創造した」
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.93,0:01:25.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記は宇宙がいつ どのように\N始まったのかは述べていません
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.61,0:01:31.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,むしろ 6つの期間にわたって地球を\N創造したプロセスに注目しています
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.11,0:01:36.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書はそれぞれの期間を\N日と呼んでいます
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.83,0:01:40.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは24時間から成る\N1日のことですか
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.95,0:01:45.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ 聖書中の「日」に\N当たるヘブライ語は
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.06,0:01:48.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,さまざまな時間の長さを\N指すことがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.96,0:01:52.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記は創造の6日間全体のことを
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.47,0:01:57.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバ神が地と天を造った日」\Nとも呼んでいます
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.01,0:02:01.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世1章のそれぞれの「日」は
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.73,0:02:05.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,かなり長い期間だったに違いありません
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.11,0:02:11.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,筆者はどんな視点で\N創造の期間を書きましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.69,0:02:17.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,地上にいる人が観察したという\N視点に立って書きました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.49,0:02:21.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしその場にいたら\N1つの期間に始まった出来事が
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.56,0:02:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後の期間にも徐々に進展していく\N様子を見ることができたでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.34,0:02:35.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,光が大気圏を通過して\N昼と夜が交互に現れます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.84,0:02:37.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,地表は水で覆われ
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.93,0:02:41.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,大気は水蒸気で満ちています
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.35,0:02:45.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,厚い雲が地表を覆っていた\N水から上昇し
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.23,0:02:49.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,広々とした空間が水と雲の間にできます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:53.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,水が引いて乾いた地面が現れ
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.82,0:02:56.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,植物が芽生えます
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.82,0:03:02.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,大気が透き通り\N太陽と月が見えるようになります
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.54,0:03:08.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,神は海の生き物と空を飛ぶ\N生き物を造ります
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.54,0:03:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後に神は陸生動物と人間を造ります
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.10,0:03:26.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記の記録は聖書の\N次の言葉と調和しています
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.60,0:03:31.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,「言うまでもなく 家は全て\N誰かによって造られるのであり
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.19,0:03:35.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,全てのものを造ったのは神です」
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.53,0:03:39.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書は細かな点に触れてはいませんが
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.53,0:03:44.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,創造に関する記録は\N論理的で筋が通っています
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:48.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書はほかのさまざまな疑問にも
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.54,0:03:52.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,論理的で筋が通った答えを述べています
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.59,0:03:55.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,地球が存在しているのはなぜか
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.80,0:03:58.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,人は何のために生きているのか
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.97,0:04:01.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,将来はどうなるのか
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.55,0:04:03.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の答えを知りたい方は
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.85,0:04:07.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,jw.org®をご覧になるか
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.39,0:04:09.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,オンラインで訪問を申し込み
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.62,0:04:21.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご都合の良い時間と場所を\Nお知らせいただくこともできます
